				      The function <m>g : S \to S</m> given by <xref ref="T-act-changing-inverse-does-it-2">Table</xref>, where <m>S = \{0, 1, 2, 3, 4 \}</m>.
    				</p>
        <table xml:id="T-act-changing-inverse-does-it-2">
          <title>Values of <m>y = g(x)</m>.</title>
          <tabular>
            <row bottom="minor">
              <cell>
                <m>x</m>
              </cell>
              <cell>0</cell>
              <cell>1</cell>
              <cell>2</cell>
              <cell>3</cell>
              <cell>4</cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell>
                <m>g(x)</m>
              </cell>
              <cell>4</cell>
              <cell>0</cell>
              <cell>3</cell>
              <cell>1</cell>
              <cell>2</cell>
            </row>
          </tabular>
        </table>
      </statement>
      <hint/>
      <answer/>
      <solution/>
    </task>
    <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="act-changing-inverse-does-it-task-2">
      <statement>
        <p>
						The function <m>p</m> given by <m>p(t) = 7 - \frac{3}{5}t</m>.  Assume that the domain and codomain of <m>p</m> are both <q>all real numbers</q>.
					</p>
      </statement>
      <hint/>
      <answer/>
      <solution/>
    </task>
    <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="act-changing-inverse-does-it-task-3">
      <statement>
        <p>
						The function <m>q</m> given by <m>q(t) = 7 - \frac{3}{5}t^4</m>.  Assume that the domain and codomain of <m>q</m> are both <q>all real numbers</q>.
					</p>
      </statement>
      <hint/>
